 the groundwork for future inquiries into the development of museums outside of the Euro-American milieu.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMuseumsxCollection managementxHistoryxTurkeyxTurkey. 0aMuseumsxCollection managementzTurkeyxHistory. 0aMuseumsxHistoryxTurkey. 0aMuseumszTurkeyxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  a1874 antiquities law.  aabdlaziz.  aabdlhamid ii.  aabdlhamid.  aantique weapons.  aantiquities.  aarchaeology.  aartifacts.  acameras.  achurch of the hagia irene.  acollection management.  acollection.  acolonial narratives.  aconquest.  adisplay.  aempire.  ahistory.  aidentity.  aimperial armory.  aimperial museum.  aimperialism.  aislam.  amiddle east.  amilitary storehouse.  amilitary.  amuseum administration.  amuseum exhibits.  amuseums.  anational identity.  aottoman empire.  aottoman museums.  arailroads.  arelics.  aspoils of war.  aspolia.  atechnology.  aturkey.  aturks.  awar.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092856540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520928565423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520928565/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles